S3.description:
#studywithme  #스윗미 #공부
 
[더보기란]
📢 Time table
* Every day : 08:00~24:00(Live), 24:00~08:00(Recorded)
* 상태표시 : 상단 현재시각 옆에 빨간불 들어오면 Live, 없으면 녹화방송(식사 및 기타)
* 12시~13시(점심식사), 18시~19시(저녁식사)
* 정기휴무 : 토요일
* 새벽방송은 녹방
* 창문속 화면은 서울의 실시간 중계입니다.

📢 시험 및 기간
* 23년 2월부터 감정평가사 준비중 
* [박문각 감정평가사]에서 지원을 받아 온라인으로 학습하고 있습니다.
* 종종 화면에 노출되는 강의 저작권에 관한 사항은 [박문각 감정평가사]로부터 사전 동의를 받았습니다.

📢 사용가능한 명령어
✔️  출첵 명령어 :  출첵,  ㅊㅊ, 복귀, ㅂㄱ
✔️  퇴첵 명령어 : 퇴첵,  ㅌㅊ, 외출, ㅇㅊ
✔️ 입장 명령어 : 중간고사방, 기말고사방, 모의고사방, 입시방, 공시방, 고시방, 학교방, 샤워방,
                               공부방, 인강방, 학원방, 과제방, 독서방, 운동방, 휴식방, 식사방, 간식방, 꿀잠방
✔️ 명언 명령어 : 명언-1에서부터 명언-41까지 예)명언-7
✔️ 명령어는 한 타임에 최대 3개정도만 해주세요. (도배는 타인에게 방해될수 있어요)

📢 information for foreigners
✔️ Hi, I am ziho in Korea. let’s study hard together!
✔️ I prepare for the exam once a year. If I pass the exam, I will be qualified to evaluate
      all real estate value in Korea.
✔️ Please chat during breaks, excluding commands and greetings.
✔️ commands : in, out, meal, study, break, back

📢 Product
✔️ 지워지는 볼펜 : 프릭션(4색 멀티 0.38mm, 노크존 0.7mm, 노크존 우드 0.7mm)
✔️ 지워지는 형광펜 : 프릭션(라이트, 라이트 네츄럴) 
✔️ 샤프 : 펜텔 그래프1000(+ain샤프심)
✔️ 컴퓨터 : LG 올인원
✔️ 스피커 : 미디플러스 MI3 II 3인치
✔️ 키보드, 마우스 : 로지텍 K380s, M350s
✔️ 계산기 : fx-9860g3
✔️ 독서대 : 셀프제작(가로 80cm)
✔️ 책상 : e-smart
✔️ 의자 : 시디즈 T50

📢 '열품타'를 운영하고 있습니다. 주20시간/주40시간
       - '공부하는지호'로 검색
       - 자세한건 커뮤니티 [열품타 공지]글을 참고해주세요.

📢 기타 내용
✔️ 출첵, 퇴첵 확인이 필요하신 분은 ‘좌측 상단의 시청기록-실시간 채팅’란에서 가능.
✔️ 채팅창 열어놓고 하시는분은, 불편한 채팅이 올라올시 '개인차단'기능을 이용하세요.

✔️ 나이, 성별 비공개
✔️ 악의적으로 반말, 비속어, 비아냥 거리시는 분은 바로 숨김처리합니다.
✔️ 과도한 친목으로 번질수 있는 인스타, 줌 등의 공유는 금지합니다. 

✔️ 디데이 적용을 원하시는분은 하루 전 업로드된 라이브에상에 댓글로 시험일/회차를 남겨주세요.
✔️ 노트북 배경화면은 강의 저작권 보호를 위해 사진으로써 연출한 것입니다.
✔️ 학습시간 시작과 끝에는 학교종이 울려요.
✔️ 채팅은 쉬는시간에 봐요.
✔️ 지호의 아침 지각벌금 : 누적 8000원

📢 문의

Hi!

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. 🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy.

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡

If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

*🌸 Welcome to my “Study with Me” Livestream! 🌸*

*🔥 What to Expect:*
• Study Method: We use the Pomodoro technique (50 min study + 10 min break) - A time management method where we study with focus for 50 minutes, then take a 10-minute break. This will be called Session- 1. An alarm will notify us when the timer is complete.
• Duration: 12 hours with 12 sessions.
• Background: Real ASMR sounds (🌧️ Rain, ⛈️ Thunder, 🔥 Fire crackling, 🌿 Nature Sounds).
• Chat: Interaction during breaks (I’ll reply in chat, not via voice, as some prefer silent study sessions)

👾 We have a Chat Bot, type the following commands in chat:
🤖 !start – Begin your study session.
🤖 !target "your target" – Set your study goal. Example: !target 2 chapters
🤖 !done "your target" – Mark tasks as completed. Example: !done 2 chapters
🤖 !break – Take a break when needed.
🤖 !points – Track your study hours & points. 🏆
📌You can also drop your to-do list in Comment & track your progress!

S42.description:
Hi! This study with me stream is a replay of my old lives. I hope this stream will help you study and keep our community connected when I am not live. You can get my live study schedule here:https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1eBb0mJkfsQXCOITzMmaSwdIpSS4Mnvg8pYr9EwOv--o/edit?usp=sharing or type !schedule. If you have any suggestions for the stream, please let me know. Thank you! Don't forget to like & subscribe 𓍢ִ໋ ͙֒  All the best with your studies! ♡ 

Goal: 1000 likes, 10k subs and 20 members

Live Chat Rules:
🌙 chat only in English so everyone can understand each other.
🌙 minimal chatting while the study session is going on.
🌙 be respectful and kind.
🌙 no spamming, advertising and inappropriate behaviour.

Commands:
⭐ !quote - motivational quotes
⭐ !genie - start counting your study time. If u just joined, type !genie. No time will be added yet. When the break starts, type !genie again to add 1 hour. If it fails, type !genie again after 10 mins. If Streamlabs still isn't counting properly, notify our mods and they will manually add the hour for u. Otherwise, please avoid chatting outside of break ^-^ 
⭐ !remove - to remove an hour from your total study time.
⭐ !target (task) - to add a task to your to-do list.
⭐ !done (task) - when you finish your task.
⭐ !forest (code) (duration) (tree name) - to share your forest code.
⭐ !foresthelp - to get more commands for Forest's FAQ
⭐ !top - top users with the most study hours.
⭐ !discord - to get our discord server invite link.
⭐ !schedule - to get the link to my live schedule.

This is the study with me session and here we use the pomodoro technique for studying. 💭Thoughts and purpose of this channel:

In today's world it's so difficult to congregate your focus for a particular work. There are distractions everywhere and it's too easy to lose your self-consciousness to these distractions. During this period of engrossment, It becomes essential for us to take back our consciousness and get out of the pool of distractions which seems pleasureful to swim in but is slowly submerging us into it. Best way to avoid these things is to be conscious and engage yourself in the activity which is actually important to you. It is the exact purpose of this channel. This channel is rooted onto the foundation of making progress and helping other to make progress. 

Personally, I get motivated by watching other people study. I've been watching these "study with me" sessions of other youtubers from long ago (until I started my own), and being honest, it helped me a lot. I am heartily thankful for those youtubers who helped me to make my study effective and I can confront that they created a positive impact in my life. Since I'm in their place right now, I can't be more happier than to be able to make the same positive impact on other people's life. There is a quotation saying "Helping others is the way we help ourselves". I feel that helping people and being able to make a positive impact in other people's life is the greatest thing a human can do. So, I think that you have understood the soul purpose of creating this channel.
